<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Yardage Chart </h2>



<p>First let=E2=80=99s break down the yardage. When you look at a sewing pa=
ttern, whether a physical tissue paper pattern in an envelope or a pattern =
you download, it will specify the yardage needed for your project. </p>



<p>One yard of fabric equals 36=E2=80=B3 or 91.5cm. But, what if your patte=
rn calls for 1/4 or 5/8 yard? How many inches is that?</p>



