<p>Let=E2=80=99s break it down into steps:</p>



<p><strong>Step One:</strong> Locate the fabric width column labeled <stron=
g>44-45=E2=80=B3</strong>. </p>



<p><strong>Step Two: </strong>Come straight down that column to the <strong=
>2-3/4</strong> yardage. </p>



<p><strong>Step Three:</strong> Then go straight across (to the left) to th=
e <strong>35-36=E2=80=B3 </strong>column. There you will see <strong>3-3/8 =
</strong>yards. </p>



<p>So, you will need 3-3/8 yards of 35-36=E2=80=B3 fabric for your project.=
 </p>



