I can't even begin to tell you how many times I've done that in the past! T=
o be fair, no one ever told me &quot;here's how to properly hold and use yo=
ur seam ripper&quot;. I was doing it wrong for years!=20

Here are two tips for using your seam ripper:=20

1. Always make sure the round plastic tip is between your layers of fabric =
and on the bottom of your work.=20
2. Take your time. It may be necessary to pick one little stitch out in ord=
er to get your seam ripper between really tight stitches.=20

You'll find this and other beginner friendly sewing tips, tutorials and pat=
terns on the Hooked on Sewing blog!=20

You can easily subscribe to my newsletter using the link in my bio!=20

